<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="267" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,402,428]" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2022" box="[344,502,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Nigripeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cali">
<emphasis box="[344,502,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="267">Nigripeza cali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is remarkable for the short and thick ejaculatory duct running to a stout sperm pump with a very short ejaculatory apodeme. Females are unknown but the external features of this species, especially the unusually dark frontal vitta, seem distinctive.
</paragraph>
